1
00:00:12,688 --> 00:00:14,906
What are you doing here?

2
00:00:16,759 --> 00:00:17,826
What?

3
00:00:17,826 --> 00:00:20,453
What brought you guys here?

4
00:00:20,453 --> 00:00:22,255
Hyung Dae Yeong invited us.

5
00:00:22,255 --> 00:00:24,790
Hyung? Invited?

6
00:00:24,790 --> 00:00:25,926
Yes.

7
00:00:25,926 --> 00:00:28,462
Ji Seong told him that he was stressed out from studying,

8
00:00:28,462 --> 00:00:32,361
so Hyung Dae Yeong invited Ji Seong here to get some fresh air.

9
00:00:32,361 --> 00:00:34,575
That's why we're here.

10
00:00:35,277 --> 00:00:39,486
Ji Seong is wearing the new O'NEILL training suit for this day.

11
00:00:39,486 --> 00:00:41,357
Nice!

12
00:00:42,551 --> 00:00:44,218
Well...

13
00:00:44,218 --> 00:00:47,045
Everyone is dressed nicely.

14
00:00:47,045 --> 00:00:50,097
But you're no match for Ji Seong.

15
00:00:50,097 --> 00:00:51,784
Look.

16
00:00:52,644 --> 00:00:55,346
Ji Seong looks the best, doesn't he?

17
00:01:00,236 --> 00:01:02,320
What about the rest of you?

18
00:01:02,320 --> 00:01:04,697
Did President invite you guys too?

19
00:01:04,697 --> 00:01:06,549
Ji Seong brought them here.

20
00:01:06,549 --> 00:01:09,417
Hyung Dae Yeong said Ji Seong could bring his friends.

21
00:01:09,417 --> 00:01:10,546
Right, Hyung Dae Yeong?

22
00:01:10,546 --> 00:01:12,005
Sure, good job!

23
00:01:12,005 --> 00:01:14,032
Great job, Bro.

24
00:01:26,478 --> 00:01:30,448
[Best Mistake 3]

25
00:01:30,448 --> 00:01:33,516
One, two, three.

26
00:01:33,516 --> 00:01:34,744
Next pose.

27
00:01:34,744 --> 00:01:36,961
One, two, three.

28
00:01:37,631 --> 00:01:39,724
Let's take more pictures over there.

29
00:01:45,698 --> 00:01:47,524
There are so many bugs.

30
00:01:47,524 --> 00:01:51,084
Seol, do you want to take a selfie together?

31
00:01:52,287 --> 00:01:54,572
Huh? Oh, sure.

32
00:02:01,463 --> 00:02:04,006
Bugs. You have a lot of bugs on you.

33
00:02:11,231 --> 00:02:14,383
I want to take a photo with the scenery.

34
00:02:15,978 --> 00:02:17,995
I'll take one for you.

35
00:02:22,484 --> 00:02:25,386
One, two, three.

36
00:02:26,530 --> 00:02:28,380
Do you want to check?

37
00:02:29,032 --> 00:02:30,792
Wow, it's a great picture.

38
00:02:30,792 --> 00:02:33,361
You take good pictures.

39
00:02:33,361 --> 00:02:35,488
Do you like it?

40
00:02:38,801 --> 00:02:40,094
He's not good at it.

41
00:02:40,094 --> 00:02:42,954
The picture is great because of the model.

42
00:03:03,175 --> 00:03:08,967
What if I have a crush on you?

43
00:03:10,616 --> 00:03:12,675
What are you talking about?

44
00:03:12,675 --> 00:03:16,119
You like Do Ye Seok.

45
00:03:16,119 --> 00:03:16,822
I—

46
00:03:16,846 --> 00:03:19,307
I like Kim Yeon Du.

47
00:03:20,643 --> 00:03:23,268
Bye. I'm going.

48
00:03:32,680 --> 00:03:34,672
Kim Yeon Du.

49
00:03:35,474 --> 00:03:37,101
Let's start the three-people four-legged race.

50
00:03:37,101 --> 00:03:38,501
Gather around.

51
00:03:38,501 --> 00:03:40,344
Okay.

52
00:03:45,834 --> 00:03:46,559
Okay.

53
00:03:46,559 --> 00:03:51,153
We will now start the three-people four-legged race!

54
00:03:51,153 --> 00:03:53,132
Yay!

55
00:03:54,551 --> 00:03:56,918
The referee will be Ji Seong.

56
00:03:56,918 --> 00:03:59,421
Gather in your groups.

57
00:04:04,694 --> 00:04:07,045
Why, of all people...

58
00:04:07,045 --> 00:04:09,123
Look who's talking.

59
00:04:10,342 --> 00:04:11,201
All right.

60
00:04:11,201 --> 00:04:13,827
Everyone, tie the ropes around your ankles.

61
00:04:13,827 --> 00:04:16,140
You'll be disqualified if you trip.

62
00:04:16,140 --> 00:04:21,390
♫ The two of us that seems 100 percent close and perfect ♫

63
00:04:21,390 --> 00:04:23,553
Hey. Stand over here.

64
00:04:23,553 --> 00:04:25,005
Come here.

65
00:04:25,005 --> 00:04:26,033
What are you doing?

66
00:04:26,033 --> 00:04:30,460
The strongest member should be in the middle.

67
00:04:30,460 --> 00:04:32,550
Tie the rope.

68
00:04:32,550 --> 00:04:37,610
♫ I'm going forward to you with steering helm ♫

69
00:04:37,610 --> 00:04:38,837
Tie the ribbon properly.

70
00:04:38,837 --> 00:04:40,960
This is the prettiest ribbon tie-up.

71
00:04:40,960 --> 00:04:43,910
♫ Run faster toward me ♫

72
00:04:43,910 --> 00:04:44,785
Left foot first.

73
00:04:44,785 --> 00:04:47,769
One, two.

74
00:04:47,769 --> 00:04:49,080
Go!

75
00:04:49,080 --> 00:04:50,432
One, two.

76
00:04:50,432 --> 00:04:51,825
One, two.

77
00:04:51,825 --> 00:04:53,076
One, two.

78
00:04:53,076 --> 00:04:54,750
One, two.

79
00:04:54,750 --> 00:04:57,800
♫ Even if it hurts, we still cross the lines ♫

80
00:04:57,800 --> 00:05:00,573
Ji Hyeon Ho is disqualified!

81
00:05:00,573 --> 00:05:01,835
One, two.

82
00:05:01,835 --> 00:05:04,380
One, two.

83
00:05:04,380 --> 00:05:08,710
♫ It's getting perfect again ♫

84
00:05:08,710 --> 00:05:11,810
♫ Like being possessed by something ♫

85
00:05:11,810 --> 00:05:13,755
You can't even put one foot forward at a time?

86
00:05:13,755 --> 00:05:15,665
Hey, was this all you could do, staying in the middle?

87
00:05:15,665 --> 00:05:17,751
And I told you to tie the rope tightly.

88
00:05:17,751 --> 00:05:18,693
The ribbon isn't even pretty.

89
00:05:18,693 --> 00:05:19,636
You think this is loose?

90
00:05:19,636 --> 00:05:22,312
You think this is tight? You're supposed to tie it like this.

91
00:05:22,312 --> 00:05:23,590
Are you blind? Look.

92
00:05:23,590 --> 00:05:26,010
She almost got hurt.

93
00:05:27,211 --> 00:05:30,030
I'm warning you.

94
00:05:30,030 --> 00:05:32,740
Don't cross the line.

95
00:05:32,740 --> 00:05:35,209
Right back at you.

96
00:05:38,238 --> 00:05:39,531
Hey.

97
00:05:39,531 --> 00:05:41,299
Both of you, don't cross the line.

98
00:05:41,299 --> 00:05:44,809
If you cross the line, you'll be disqualified.

99
00:05:44,809 --> 00:05:47,790
Hurry, stand straight.

100
00:05:50,025 --> 00:05:50,992
Ready.

101
00:05:50,992 --> 00:05:53,394
Go!

102
00:06:03,238 --> 00:06:05,190
You should've just let me go.

103
00:06:28,472 --> 00:06:30,457
My first... My first kiss...

104
00:06:30,457 --> 00:06:33,050
Don't go easy on me.

105
00:06:33,050 --> 00:06:35,650
Ready, go!

106
00:06:47,582 --> 00:06:49,350
- Yeon Du!
- Yeon Du!

107
00:06:49,350 --> 00:06:51,750
- Are you okay?
- Are you okay?

108
00:07:02,013 --> 00:07:04,365
I fell too.

109
00:07:16,361 --> 00:07:19,229
We're crashing another club's trip, but this is so much fun.

110
00:07:19,229 --> 00:07:20,348
Right?

111
00:07:20,348 --> 00:07:21,340
It is fun.

112
00:07:21,340 --> 00:07:23,308
It feels like I'm on vacation.

113
00:07:23,308 --> 00:07:26,302
Being here makes me feel like I'm back in Korea for real.

114
00:07:26,302 --> 00:07:27,981
Even the air is different from the US.

115
00:07:27,981 --> 00:07:29,916
Okay then, cheers!

116
00:07:29,916 --> 00:07:30,984
Yes.

117
00:07:30,984 --> 00:07:33,559
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

118
00:07:35,463 --> 00:07:38,489
Yeon Du. Have a glass of drink.

119
00:07:38,489 --> 00:07:40,960
I'm trying to cut back on drinking.

120
00:07:40,960 --> 00:07:42,969
Why cutting back? Drinking is great.

121
00:07:42,969 --> 00:07:44,914
You can start cutting back tomorrow. Please?

122
00:07:44,914 --> 00:07:46,757
Just today.

123
00:07:51,889 --> 00:07:54,381
- Here you go—
- I'll drink!
- I'll drink!

124
00:07:55,509 --> 00:07:57,919
Can you hold your liquor?

125
00:07:57,919 --> 00:07:59,329
Is that why you keep doing this?

126
00:07:59,329 --> 00:08:02,588
Well, I love to drink.

127
00:08:05,160 --> 00:08:07,969
Then drink out of the bottle.

128
00:08:07,969 --> 00:08:10,797
I've got to drink this.

129
00:08:13,418 --> 00:08:15,361
Hyeon Ho doesn't know his opponent.

130
00:08:15,361 --> 00:08:18,154
Ye Seok can drink heavily.

131
00:08:19,649 --> 00:08:21,450
Hyeon Ho can hold his liquor too.

132
00:08:21,450 --> 00:08:24,536
If he wants to, he can outdrink anyone under the table.

133
00:08:24,536 --> 00:08:26,997
Ye Seok can drink like a whale.

134
00:08:26,997 --> 00:08:28,275
Got it?

135
00:08:28,275 --> 00:08:29,617
A whale?

136
00:08:29,617 --> 00:08:31,986
Hyeon Ho can drink like a hippo.

137
00:08:31,986 --> 00:08:33,755
You know that hippos are terrifying, right?

138
00:08:33,755 --> 00:08:36,648
Ye Seok drinks alcohol like water.

139
00:08:36,648 --> 00:08:38,310
Hyeon Ho is an alcoholic.

140
00:08:38,310 --> 00:08:40,986
He can drink a lot because he drinks every day.

141
00:08:40,986 --> 00:08:44,139
He came to drink all the booze here.

142
00:08:44,139 --> 00:08:46,233
Ji Seong, you've drunk too much.

143
00:08:46,233 --> 00:08:49,844
Stop drinking. Let's take a walk to sober up.

144
00:08:49,844 --> 00:08:50,747
Okay.

145
00:08:50,747 --> 00:08:53,074
Ji Seong likes taking walks.

146
00:08:54,126 --> 00:08:55,735
Let's go.

147
00:08:57,337 --> 00:08:59,596
You've had enough.

148
00:09:00,356 --> 00:09:01,765
Seol.

149
00:09:01,765 --> 00:09:02,651
Are you getting drunk?

150
00:09:02,651 --> 00:09:05,335
No. Not at all.

151
00:09:43,499 --> 00:09:46,417
Guys, let's say cheers.

152
00:09:47,153 --> 00:09:49,421
Fill your glasses.

153
00:09:52,459 --> 00:09:53,959
What?

154
00:09:53,959 --> 00:09:56,202
They're all empty.

155
00:09:56,202 --> 00:09:59,296
Vice President! Can you get alcohol from the fridge on your way here?

156
00:09:59,296 --> 00:10:00,791
We're out.

157
00:10:00,791 --> 00:10:02,960
I think we drank it all.

158
00:10:02,960 --> 00:10:04,645
There are no snacks either.

159
00:10:04,645 --> 00:10:08,297
We haven't had much. We're out of alcohol and snacks already?

160
00:10:08,297 --> 00:10:13,025
Yeon Du. We didn't have enough money for alcohol and food?

161
00:10:13,025 --> 00:10:16,155
How strange... I thought I had bought plenty.

162
00:10:16,155 --> 00:10:18,092
Maybe we forgot to load them in the car.

163
00:10:18,092 --> 00:10:20,611
We bought several boxes of drinks.

164
00:10:20,611 --> 00:10:22,229
Oh, well.

165
00:10:22,229 --> 00:10:24,373
Let's go out and get some more nearby.

166
00:10:25,533 --> 00:10:27,134
I'll go.

167
00:10:27,134 --> 00:10:29,087
You don't know how to drive.

168
00:10:29,087 --> 00:10:31,114
We have to take the car to get booze.

169
00:10:31,114 --> 00:10:33,273
I'll go with you.

170
00:10:39,772 --> 00:10:43,431
No. I'll go.

171
00:10:43,431 --> 00:10:47,329
Kim Yeon Du and I are in charge of shopping.

172
00:10:49,307 --> 00:10:52,609
You've been drinking. You can't drive.

173
00:10:52,609 --> 00:10:54,795
Sit down, both of you!

174
00:11:05,323 --> 00:11:09,482
We could've gone for a drive to buy if we hadn't drunk.

175
00:11:09,482 --> 00:11:10,578
Right, Seol?

176
00:11:10,578 --> 00:11:11,980
We already had drinks.

177
00:11:11,980 --> 00:11:13,206
You and I, both of us.

178
00:11:13,206 --> 00:11:17,432
Who is sober and can drive?

179
00:11:17,432 --> 00:11:19,611
I'll go.

180
00:11:24,317 --> 00:11:26,260
I didn't drink.

181
00:11:26,260 --> 00:11:27,945
And I know how to drive.

182
00:11:27,945 --> 00:11:28,996
That's great.

183
00:11:28,996 --> 00:11:32,107
I'll go with her.

184
00:11:46,673 --> 00:11:49,074
Unnie Se Hui, are you ready?

185
00:11:49,074 --> 00:11:50,093
Yes.

186
00:11:50,093 --> 00:11:53,830
I need to go to the bathroom first.

187
00:11:53,830 --> 00:11:55,832
Do you want to wait in the car?

188
00:11:55,832 --> 00:11:58,033
Sure. I'll wait in the car.

189
00:11:58,033 --> 00:12:00,136
No rush.

190
00:12:30,717 --> 00:12:33,585
Unnie Se Hui. What do we do?

191
00:12:33,585 --> 00:12:36,563
I forgot my wallet.

192
00:12:38,266 --> 00:12:39,842
Can you pay for these?

193
00:12:39,842 --> 00:12:41,760
I'll pay you back when we get back.

194
00:12:41,760 --> 00:12:43,329
Is that okay?

195
00:12:43,329 --> 00:12:45,597
Sure.

196
00:12:49,277 --> 00:12:50,437
Oh no...

197
00:12:50,437 --> 00:12:52,538
I think I also forgot my wallet.

198
00:12:52,538 --> 00:12:53,740
Oh, really?

199
00:12:53,740 --> 00:12:56,016
Oh... What should we do?

200
00:12:56,016 --> 00:12:57,702
We already picked out everything.

201
00:12:57,702 --> 00:12:59,395
I'll quickly go and grab it.

202
00:12:59,395 --> 00:13:01,189
Wait here a little bit, Yeon Du.

203
00:13:01,189 --> 00:13:03,182
- Here?
- Yes.

204
00:13:03,182 --> 00:13:05,718
Look around and see if there's anything else we need.

205
00:13:05,718 --> 00:13:06,961
I'll be right back.

206
00:13:06,961 --> 00:13:08,913
Oh, but...

207
00:13:08,913 --> 00:13:12,127
My phone is charging in your car. How am I going to contact...

208
00:13:12,127 --> 00:13:13,835
It'll only take 30 minutes.

209
00:13:13,835 --> 00:13:16,812
You won't need to contact me.

210
00:13:17,639 --> 00:13:20,148
I'll be back as quick as I can.

211
00:13:21,626 --> 00:13:24,928
Okay, I'll wait here.

212
00:13:34,156 --> 00:13:36,098
- Hey.
- What?

213
00:13:36,098 --> 00:13:37,951
Do you know what you should do?

214
00:13:37,951 --> 00:13:39,752
What?

215
00:13:39,752 --> 00:13:41,495
A tattoo.

216
00:13:42,321 --> 00:13:44,722
What? You're back so soon?

217
00:13:44,722 --> 00:13:47,434
Why are you alone? Where is Yeon Du?

218
00:13:47,434 --> 00:13:51,237
We forgot our wallets. So I came back to grab it.

219
00:13:51,237 --> 00:13:53,440
Yeon Du is at the supermarket.

220
00:13:57,454 --> 00:13:59,096
What?

221
00:13:59,096 --> 00:14:03,050
Yeon Du is at the supermarket alone?

222
00:14:09,482 --> 00:14:11,992
What's taking her so long?

223
00:14:11,992 --> 00:14:14,478
She said she'd be quick.

224
00:14:22,928 --> 00:14:24,196
Oh, right.

225
00:14:24,196 --> 00:14:26,631
We had some money left.

226
00:14:26,631 --> 00:14:28,783
Thank goodness.

227
00:14:36,134 --> 00:14:38,936
I'll just wait here.

228
00:14:45,802 --> 00:14:48,158
Seol: Kim Yeon Du, Se Hui said you're at the supermarket alone.

229
00:14:48,182 --> 00:14:49,330
Are you okay?

230
00:14:49,330 --> 00:14:50,572
Everything is fine, right?

231
00:14:50,572 --> 00:14:51,866
Juho: Yeon Du, we'll pick you up.

232
00:14:51,866 --> 00:14:53,501
Which supermarket is it?

233
00:14:53,501 --> 00:14:56,004
Hyeon Ho: Kim Yeon Du, where are you? Call me back!

234
00:14:56,004 --> 00:14:58,189
Ye Seok: Yeon Du, did you meet Jin Se Hui?

235
00:14:58,189 --> 00:14:59,841
Which supermarket are you at?

236
00:14:59,841 --> 00:15:02,760
Kim Yeon Du, text me back, please!

237
00:15:18,801 --> 00:15:21,786
A girl like you have no idea how I feel.

238
00:15:21,786 --> 00:15:23,922
The feeling of being all alone.

239
00:15:25,792 --> 00:15:29,360
Do Ye Seok and Ji Hyeon Ho are all next to you.

240
00:15:31,690 --> 00:15:37,967
Kim Yeon Du, I want you to feel how miserable it feels to be alone.

241
00:15:48,606 --> 00:15:50,490
Seol.

242
00:15:51,442 --> 00:15:54,153
When did Se Hui leave with the wallet?

243
00:15:54,153 --> 00:15:56,679
About 30 minutes ago.

244
00:15:56,679 --> 00:15:59,708
She should be here by now.

245
00:16:03,797 --> 00:16:05,806
What's this? Where is Kim Yeon Du?

246
00:16:05,806 --> 00:16:08,040
- What about Yeon Du?
- Why is she not with you?

247
00:16:08,040 --> 00:16:09,501
You couldn't find Yeon Du?

248
00:16:09,501 --> 00:16:12,428
Se Hui. Why didn't you answer your phone?

249
00:16:12,428 --> 00:16:13,940
She's not here, either?

250
00:16:13,940 --> 00:16:15,683
I thought she had left without me.

251
00:16:15,683 --> 00:16:18,101
What? Tell the truth.

252
00:16:18,101 --> 00:16:22,913
We both forgot our wallets, and Yeon Du asked me to bring her wallet.

253
00:16:22,913 --> 00:16:24,943
So I grabbed her wallet and went back to the supermarket.

254
00:16:24,943 --> 00:16:27,711
But she wasn't there.

255
00:16:29,606 --> 00:16:33,448
This is why I told her to come with me.

256
00:16:36,228 --> 00:16:38,855
What's wrong? Did something happen?

257
00:16:38,855 --> 00:16:40,866
Did you see Yeon Du on your way back?

258
00:16:40,866 --> 00:16:41,884
Squirtle?

259
00:16:41,884 --> 00:16:44,385
Squirtle, I thought she was here.

260
00:16:44,385 --> 00:16:46,489
She went to the supermarket.

261
00:16:46,489 --> 00:16:47,749
You didn't see her outside?

262
00:16:47,749 --> 00:16:51,125
No. We didn't see her.

263
00:16:59,611 --> 00:17:03,330
Yeon Du left her phone in my car to charge it.

264
00:17:10,000 --> 00:17:13,400
Guys, let's go out and look for her.

265
00:17:13,439 --> 00:17:16,017
Where is she?

266
00:17:22,675 --> 00:17:24,142
Kim Yeon Du!

267
00:17:24,142 --> 00:17:26,169
Yeon Du!

268
00:17:28,548 --> 00:17:30,457
Man...

269
00:17:30,457 --> 00:17:32,817
It's too dark.

270
00:17:33,769 --> 00:17:35,637
Kim Yeon Du!

271
00:17:42,962 --> 00:17:45,939
It's already been 30 minutes.

272
00:17:46,716 --> 00:17:50,050
Maybe something happened to her.

273
00:17:57,284 --> 00:17:58,368
The supermarket's location...

274
00:17:58,368 --> 00:18:00,890
[Recent destination]

275
00:18:03,241 --> 00:18:05,542
Why isn't there a record?

276
00:18:25,822 --> 00:18:32,173
Kim Yeon Du, I want you to feel how miserable it feels to be alone.

277
00:18:55,293 --> 00:18:58,228
You came back for this?

278
00:18:58,228 --> 00:18:59,514
You got it all wrong—

279
00:18:59,514 --> 00:19:02,157
You're the worst.

280
00:19:03,459 --> 00:19:05,109
What?

281
00:19:05,109 --> 00:19:08,204
I didn't know you were this bad.

282
00:19:09,440 --> 00:19:15,424
If something happens to Yeon Du, I'll make you pay.

283
00:19:30,219 --> 00:19:33,271
The countryside is cold at night.

284
00:19:33,271 --> 00:19:35,674
Oh, it's so cold.

285
00:19:40,404 --> 00:19:42,764
[Myungpoom Makgeolli]

286
00:19:44,817 --> 00:19:47,277
Should I drink some?

287
00:19:47,945 --> 00:19:51,355
I think alcohol will warm me up.

288
00:19:52,483 --> 00:19:55,425
Yeah. I'm thirsty too, so I'll drink...

289
00:20:09,758 --> 00:20:12,801
Hey! Ji Hyeon Ho.

290
00:20:15,806 --> 00:20:23,626
You have no idea why we broke up.

291
00:20:25,108 --> 00:20:28,093
Of course, you don't

292
00:20:28,093 --> 00:20:31,129
because I didn't tell you.

293
00:20:32,115 --> 00:20:34,642
But you didn't tell me either.

294
00:20:34,642 --> 00:20:36,652
I will never tell you.

295
00:20:36,652 --> 00:20:39,029
Never, never, never, never, never.

296
00:20:39,029 --> 00:20:41,139
I won't tell you.

297
00:20:43,250 --> 00:20:45,143
No...

298
00:20:46,086 --> 00:20:48,412
I can't tell you.

299
00:20:50,533 --> 00:20:53,630
How can I?

300
00:20:56,489 --> 00:20:58,948
Hyeon Ho.

301
00:20:58,948 --> 00:21:01,301
Ji Hyeon Ho!

302
00:21:02,019 --> 00:21:04,179
Are you listening to me?

303
00:21:04,179 --> 00:21:06,305
Kim Yeon Du!

304
00:21:08,976 --> 00:21:11,453
Where on earth is she?

305
00:21:11,453 --> 00:21:12,605
Kim Yeon Du!

306
00:21:12,605 --> 00:21:15,499
Are you listening to me?

307
00:21:15,499 --> 00:21:16,709
Ji Hyeon Ho!

308
00:21:16,709 --> 00:21:18,510
Kim Yeon Du?

309
00:21:22,581 --> 00:21:26,599
Listen, I'm not just saying it.

310
00:21:26,599 --> 00:21:28,554
I'm not drunk at all.

311
00:21:28,554 --> 00:21:30,780
Kim Yeon Du!

312
00:21:30,780 --> 00:21:32,582
Huh?

313
00:21:32,582 --> 00:21:34,459
Hyeon Ho?

314
00:21:40,475 --> 00:21:42,367
Are you okay?

315
00:21:42,367 --> 00:21:44,385
Are you hurt?

316
00:21:44,385 --> 00:21:47,340
I was worried sick.

317
00:21:53,112 --> 00:21:54,954
Sorry.

318
00:21:54,954 --> 00:21:57,573
I came too late again.

319
00:22:04,665 --> 00:22:06,991
Why you again?

320
00:22:07,877 --> 00:22:09,519
What?

321
00:22:09,519 --> 00:22:11,654
In high school...

322
00:22:11,654 --> 00:22:14,974
When I was locked up in the art room,

323
00:22:14,974 --> 00:22:18,871
and when I was in the motorcycle accident,

324
00:22:18,871 --> 00:22:22,281
you came to save me.

325
00:22:24,977 --> 00:22:28,129
But why you again?

326
00:22:28,129 --> 00:22:30,807
We broke up.

327
00:22:31,984 --> 00:22:35,044
Why is it you again?

328
00:22:37,814 --> 00:22:39,757
By chance...

329
00:22:40,526 --> 00:22:43,640
Were you waiting for Do Ye Seok, that punk?

330
00:22:47,249 --> 00:22:48,917
No.

331
00:22:52,130 --> 00:22:53,772
You.

332
00:22:56,367 --> 00:22:58,352
I was waiting for you.

333
00:22:58,352 --> 00:23:00,395
Ji Hyeon Ho.

334
00:23:23,903 --> 00:23:27,689
[Best Mistake 3]

335
00:23:27,689 --> 00:23:28,674
Ta-da!

336
00:23:28,674 --> 00:23:31,051
Our matching bags.

337
00:23:31,051 --> 00:23:34,820
These are super light and comfortable.

338
00:23:34,820 --> 00:23:40,800
♫ 0 percent in one day, turning around and drifting apart this much ♫

339
00:23:40,800 --> 00:23:43,400
♫ It gets back to the starting point ♫

340
00:23:43,400 --> 00:23:48,600
♫ I'm going forward to you with steering helm ♫

341
00:23:48,600 --> 00:23:49,453
[Next episode]
It was a mistake.

342
00:23:49,453 --> 00:23:50,646
Did you eat?

343
00:23:50,646 --> 00:23:52,547
With Senior Dae Yeong.

344
00:23:52,547 --> 00:23:53,958
It's none of your business.

345
00:23:53,958 --> 00:23:55,876
It's none of my business?

346
00:23:55,876 --> 00:23:59,536
I'm going to suspect you first if anything bad happens.

347
00:23:59,536 --> 00:24:02,130
What is all this?

348
00:24:02,200 --> 00:24:05,100
♫ Sometimes I know or don't know, it's strange ♫

349
00:24:05,100 --> 00:24:08,500
♫ Even if it hurts, we still cross the lines ♫

350
00:24:08,540 --> 00:24:11,951
[Best Mistake 3]
